      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): show Gemini CLI runtime auth status",
        "body": "## Summary\n- include CLI runtime auth providers in `models status` runtime-auth accounting\n- report canonical `google/*` text/default routes using `google-gemini-cli` as runtime auth routes while keeping image routes on Google API-key auth\n- update Gemini CLI OAuth setup to write the existing provider/model-scoped `agentRuntime` policy on the default Google model instead of the ignored whole-agent runtime key\n- keep CLI runtime auth checks provider-specific so `claude-cli` is not considered usable from canonical Anthropic auth/env that the CLI runtime clears\n- add regression coverage for `GEMINI_API_KEY` plus Gemini CLI OAuth profile, login-generated config patching, plugin-owned CLI runtime synthetic auth, and missing native CLI runtime auth\n\nFixes #79585.\n\n## Surface area\n- No public config schema changes.\n- No plugin API or plugin contract changes.\n- No new CLI flags, env vars, migrations, or setup surfaces.\n- This only changes `models status` auth reporting/checking and the existing Gemini CLI OAuth setup patch target.\n\n## Refresh note\nRebased onto `main` `be1273182eb971f0bdfcdd807ab7b0939e4177ca`.\n\nSigned head: `b1fa3e731609fbb5ab5d30b9ec8dbded7c963143`.\n\n## Follow-up fixes after review\n- Fixed `no-shadow` by renaming the local runtime-resolution variable.\n- Added CLI runtime providers to synthetic-auth probing, so plugin-owned runtime auth such as `claude-cli` is detected for runtime routes.\n- Kept runtime-route checks direct/provider-specific, so canonical Anthropic auth or env does not make a `claude-cli` route pass when native Claude CLI auth is missing.\n- Added regressions for both cases:\n  - `anthropic/*` routed through `claude-cli` with plugin-owned synthetic auth is usable.\n  - `anthropic/*` routed through `claude-cli` with only canonical Anthropic auth reports missing `claude-cli` and fails `--check`.\n\n## Validation\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/models/list.status.test.ts extensions/google/index.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 2 files, 39 tests passed\n- `CI=true pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/commands/models/list.status-command.ts src/commands/models/list.status.test.ts extensions/google/gemini-cli-provider.ts extensions/google/index.test.ts` -> passed\n- `CI=true pnpm exec oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/commands/models/list.status-command.ts src/commands/models/list.status.test.ts extensions/google/gemini-cli-provider.ts extensions/google/index.test.ts` -> 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` -> passed\n- `git diff --check` -> passed\n- `/home/giodl/.local/toolchains/node-v22.22.3-linux-x64/bin/codex review --base origin/main` -> no actionable correctness issues found\n- `git log --show-signature --format=\"%H %G? %s\" origin/main..HEAD` -> all 4 commits have good signatures\n\n## Remaining proof gap\nI still have not run live Gemini CLI OAuth login plus `models status --check` on this machine. The branch now has the static/focused coverage and Codex review clean, but the ClawSweeper live-proof request remains unless a maintainer accepts the remaining risk or live Gemini CLI OAuth proof is produced.\n\nNo merge performed.",
